journalEntryArray.thoughts: We did JavaScript functions and learned more about gits and github! We created dialogs for Martin's Aquarium, and I created this function to email my journal entries to myself. I am tired, and happy that it's the weekend, but overall, feeling pretty good!

We watched C37's demos. I liked the pet chore app and the fitted app. We finished our team travel site, and got more used to Git Hub. I understand more how committing different phases of work would help in a team environment. Overall, I think the team worked together well, once we found a cohesive rhythm and stride. Taking the time to learn from each other was really beneficial.
Group work can be hard when you're all at different levels.

We replicated our html automation for locations. I edited the CSS for the aquarium page. I committed several gits and feel like I'm getting the hang of GitHub!Happy it's the weekend! Ready for a break!
Worked with Globtrotters team to effectively create and merge respective branches into master.
We started using JavaScript to automate HTML from an array of objects.
We practiced more HTML automation using JavaScript.
